                                            SUBWAY ENVIRONMENT SIMULATION
                                                  SIMULATION OF
                         SES v4.1 file with a simple rail tunnel (up line, down line, one station).
                         Implicit train performance calculation.
                         Uses all forms except form 4 (fires), 6C to 6H (see the ECZ run for those) and
                         8E (explicit train speed).
                         Humidity displayed as kg/kg of dry air.
                         Supplementary print option set to 1 (add some more output).
                         Has train types with all five permutations of train motor control types 1 and 2.
                         This file has some oddities included to prove that the plots are working,
                         such as non-fire segments in the running tunnels, reversed sections,
                         jet fans and train types with odd train performance properties.
                         Do not use it as a basis for other files unless you need the weird.
                         If the runtime is extended to 1810 seconds, an ECZ estimate occurs that raises
                         simulation error 8 (failed ECZ estimate).

                                             FAN PERFORMANCE CURVE FIT COEFFICIENTS
                                             --------------------------------------
    THE COEFFICIENTS C1, C2, C3, C4 FIT THE FAN PERFORMANCE CURVE OF THE FOLLOWING EQUATION -
          C1 * (Q**3) + C2 * (Q**2) + C3 * (Q) + C4 = P
    WHERE Q IS THE AIRFLOW RATE (CFS) OF INFLOW (EXHAUST) OR OUTFLOW (SUPPLY)
          P IS THE PRESSURE HEAD IN FT**2/SEC**2
